        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_æmbaj" xml:lang="os">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>æmbaj</orth></form>
                <sense xml:lang="os-x-iron"><usg><lang/></usg><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>сверстник</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>peer</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>ровесник</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>fellow (of the same age)</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>ūj me ʽmbaj ū</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>он мой сверстник</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>he is my peer</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>cæj līʒæn ma væjjy babajy æmbajæn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>где уж бежать тому, кто (достиг) возраста дедушки</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>how can run the one who (reached) the age of grandfather</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Niger"
                            /><biblScope>143</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*ham-āyu</w>
                        <gloss><q>ровесник</q></gloss></mentioned>. В первой части — префикс %iham%i
                    → <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>æm</w></mentioned>, во второй — <ref type="xr" target="#entry_āyu-"/>
                    ‘возраст’, ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>āyu-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>ayu</w>
                        <gloss><q>возраст</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*āy(ʼ’yh)</w>
                        <gloss><q>âge</q></gloss></mentioned>
                        (<bibl><author>Gauthiot</author></bibl>), „désigne un certaine période de
                    temps, mais le sens précis manque еnсоге“ (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Gramm._sogd."/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">II 177,
                            прим.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">II 177,
                        fn.</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="zkh"><lang/>
                        <w>āy-</w>
                        <gloss><q>жизнь</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Henning._Khwar."/><biblScope>6</biblScope></bibl>). Сюда
                    же, возможно, <mentioned xml:lang="oru"><lang/>
                        <w>īmbaī</w>
                        <gloss><q>друзья</q></gloss></mentioned> (если из %i*ham-pāyu-%i, а не
                    *ham-pāθya-, как предполагает <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>I 387</biblScope></bibl>).
                    Раздвоение %im%i → mb (%iʽæmaj%i → %iæmbaj%i) такого же порядка, как в <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_kʼambec"/> ‘буйвол’ (← <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>kameči</w></mentioned>) или в <mentioned xml:lang="en"><lang/>
                        <w>chamber</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fr"><lang/>
                        <w>chambre</w></mentioned> (из %icamera%i). В данном случае раздвоению %im%i
                    → %imb%i содействовало несомненно также стремление привести слоговую границу в
                    соответствие с этимологическим сознанием, которое не могло мириться со слоговым
                    делением %iæ-maj%i.<note type="footnote" n="1"> PUT NOTE HERE </note>
                    Промежуточной формой была, вероятно, %i*æmmaj%i; ср. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_æmbūxyn"/> из %iæm-mūxyn%i, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_æmbūlyn"/> из %iæm-mūlyn%i. <bibl><author>H. W.
                            Bailey</author></bibl> дает неточное значение ‘companionʼ и ошибочно
                    возводит к %i*hambāvya%i (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"
                            /><biblScope>9</biblScope></bibl>). — Ср. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_æmgar"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kar"/>, <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_caqq"/>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*ham-āyu</w>
                        <gloss><q>peer</q></gloss></mentioned>. The first part contains the prefix
                    %iham%i → <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>æm</w></mentioned>, the second one <ref type="xr" target="#entry_āyu-"/>
                    ‘age’, cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>āyu-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>ayu</w>
                        <gloss><q>age</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*āy(ʼ’yh)</w>
                        <gloss><q>âge</q></gloss></mentioned>
                        (<bibl><author>Gauthiot</author></bibl>), „désigne un certaine période de
                    temps, mais le sens précis manque еnсоге“ (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Gramm._sogd."/><biblScope xml:lang="en">II 177,
                        fn.</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="zkh"><lang/>
                        <w>āy-</w>
                        <gloss><q>live</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Henning._Khwar."/><biblScope>6</biblScope></bibl>).
                        Perhaps<mentioned xml:lang="oru"><lang/>
                        <w>īmbaī</w>
                        <gloss><q>friends</q></gloss></mentioned> is related (if it is from
                    %i*ham-pāyu-%i and not from *ham-pāθya-, as supposed by <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>I 387</biblScope></bibl>).
                    Bifurcation %im%i → mb (%iʽæmaj%i → %iæmbaj%i) is the same as in <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_kʼambec"/> ‘buffalo’ (← <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>kameči</w></mentioned>) or in <mentioned xml:lang="en"><lang/>
                        <w>chamber</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fr"><lang/>
                        <w>chambre</w></mentioned> (from %icamera%i). In this case, the doubling
                    %im%i → %imb%i was undoubtedly facilitated by the desire to bring the syllable
                    boundary into line with the etymological conception which could not put up with
                    the syllabic division %iæ-maj%i.<note type="footnote" n="1"> PUT NOTE HERE
                    </note> Perhaps, the intermediate form was %i*æmmaj%i; cf. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_æmbūxyn"/> from %iæm-mūxyn%i, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_æmbūlyn"/> from %iæm-mūlyn%i. <bibl><author>H. W.
                            Bailey</author></bibl>gives an imprecise meaning ‘companionʼ and
                    mistakenly traces it back to %i*hambāvya%i (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"/><biblScope>9</biblScope></bibl>). — Cf.
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æmgar"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kar"
                    />, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_caqq"/>.</etym>
                <note type="footnote" xml:lang="ru" n="1">Этой же причиной вызывается, по нашему
                    мнению, удвоение конечных согласных при наращении суффиксов %i-ag%i, %i-оn%i:
                    %iqæd-ag%i ’лесной’ становится %iqæd-d-ag%i, чтобы избежать слогового деления
                    %iqæ-dag%i.</note>
                <note type="footnote" xml:lang="en" n="1">In our opinion, the same reason causes
                    doubling of final consonants accompanying the suffix augmentation %i-ag%i,
                    %i-оn%i: %iqæd-ag%i ʽforest, woodsy’ becomes %iqæd-d-ag%i, in order to avoid the
                    syllabic division %iqæ-dag%i.</note>
            </entry>
